releases.desc:
It has been a massive 18 months for DJ S.K.T's new label Stashed Music. After launching in 2017, Stashed has consistently delivered great House music, from artists such as Franky Wah, DONT BLINK, Rich Wakley, Bang Tidy, and of course DJ S.K.T.

To celebrate their landmark 50th release, label boss DJ S.K.T delivers a very special single in the form of 'Ballers'. Already the biggest track in his own club DJ sets, and with the hype it's quickly growing online, Ballers is fast becoming one of the hottest weapons in clubland, with it being dropped more than once at the recent Ultra Music Festival, in Miami.    

Stashed continues to go from strength to strength, with widespread support from leading tastemakers, club DJs across the globe and becoming one the hottest new labels on Beatport.

Also, after the successful launch of 'Stashed Sessions Podcast', look out for the launch of 'Stashed Sessions' live club events to be announced soon, with some of the world's biggest and best DJs lined up to support, Stashed are definitely a label worth paying close attention to in 2019, and beyond.

#KeepItStashed
releases.name: Ballers

releases.desc:
U.K. tastemaker DJ S.K.T has taken it upon himself to maximize the dance floor potential of New Hype's recent single and has done so to great effect. 
With discoesque chord stabs and rearranged vocals adding to the infectious groove, this take on 'Love Again' is set to rule dance floors for a long time to come.
releases.name: Love Again - DJ S.K.T Remix

releases.desc:
Regarded as one of the hottest talents in the UK club scene, DJ S.K.T is back with more brand- new music for 2021. A formidable force in the Dance Music, Toolroom fans will already be acquainted with DJ S.K.T from his previous releases on the label such as 2019's 'Raindrops' on Toolroom's Ibiza comp and more recently, mixing the latest 'Vaults Vol. 2' album.

The avid selector, DJ & label head of Stashed Music has certainly made the rounds over the past few years, from dropping the massive 2015 hit 'Take Me Away' feat. Rae to regular radio shows on KISS FM & Rinse FM. Now, DJ S.K.T makes his way back to Toolroom, with quite possibly the hottest release of the year so far with 'Call On Me'.
A definite "Hands in the air" moment record, 'Call On Me' is topped with everything you could possibly want from a Toolroom release and more. 

With a solid production from start to finish, 'Call On Me' is a huge return to form for DJ S.K.T. From the records thumping, rock steady rhythm matched to a get-up and go bassline, along with an underlining ferocious synth hook and a sublime vocal melody to tie it all together, 'Call On Me' has got it all. It's pretty obvious that DJ S.K.T has out done himself on this record, and it is without a doubt that 'Call On Me' will be THE record you will have on repeat going into 2022!
